    {3223,"Corruption: Sickness",237514,2,0,0,{"wago"},"When Corrupted Blood reaches 50%, players periodically become violently ill. They vomit and inflict $81831s1 Shadow damage to players within a $81831A1 yard long 20 degree cone in front of them. Players hit by this vile spew suffer increased Corruption.",-1,0,0,0,167,3224,3,3165,0},
    {3224,"Corruption: Malformation",136199,2,0,0,{"wago"},"When Corrupted Blood reaches 75%, the corruption is so thorough that a tentacle Malformation erupts from a player's back. The tentacle periodically casts Shadow Bolts at the player's allies, inflicting $82151s1 Shadow damage.",-1,0,0,0,167,3225,4,3165,0},
    {3225,"Corruption: Absolute",236295,2,0,0,{"wago"},"When Corrupted Blood reaches 100%, players fully transform into faceless horrors. While in this state players cannot be healed, but inflict $82170s2% additional damage and cast spells instantly.",-1,0,0,0,167,0,5,3165,0},
    {3226,"Stage One: I Will Deal With You Myself!",0,0,0,2,{"wago"},"At the outset of the battle, Sinestra is weakened from past battles and from nurturing the Twilight brood. She begins with only 60% of her maximum health, and her damage dealt is reduced by by $89350s1%.",12,3227,0,0,168,3234,1,0,0},
    {3227,"Wrack",132095,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Sinestra causes a random player to suffer Shadow damage every $89421t1 sec. for $89421d. with the damage taken increasing rapidly. When a player dispels Wrack, it bounces to two nearby allies of the afflicted player. Wrack retains its remaining duration but returns to its original damage values.",12,0,0,164,168,3228,2,3226,0},
    {3228,"Flame Breath",135805,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Sinestra unleashes a torrent of flame that sweeps across her platform, inflicting $90125s1 Fire damage to all enemies.",12,0,0,0,168,3229,3,3226,0},
    {3229,"Twilight Slicer",136202,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Sinestra summons two shadowy orbs, each of which fixates on a player and begins to pursue that player. These spheres are linked together by a cutting beam of pure twilight energy that inflicts $92852s1 Shadow damage per $92851t1 sec. to any player who comes into contact with the beam.\n\n\n\nEach sphere also pulses twilight energy, inflicting $92958s1 Shadow damage every $92957t1 sec in a $92958A1 yard radius. The orbs dissipate after $92957d.",12,0,0,48,168,3230,4,3226,0},
    {3230,"Twilight Blast",425959,2,0,2,{"wago"},"When Sinestra cannot reach anyone in melee range, she blasts an enemy for $89280s1 Shadow damage.",12,0,0,0,168,3231,5,3226,0},
    {3231,"Twilight Whelps",0,1,0,2,{"wago"},"Sinestra periodically calls forth a set of five Twilight Whelps to attack intruders.",12,3232,19295,0,168,0,6,3226,0},
    {3232,"Twilight Spit",425954,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The Twilight Whelps spit shadowy bile on their target, inflicting $89299s1 Shadow damage and increasing the target's Shadow damage taken by $89299s2%. This effect stacks.",12,0,0,1,168,3233,7,3231,0},
    {3233,"Twilight Essence",425958,2,0,2,{"wago"},"When a Twilight Whelp dies, the essence instilled in it by Sinestra leaks out, forming a bubbling puddle beneath its corpse. If this essence touches any other dead Twilight Whelp, that Whelp reanimates. Each pool of Twilight Essence expands over time. The pools inflict $88146s2 Shadow damage every $89284t1 sec.",12,0,0,1,168,0,8,3231,0},
    {3234,"Stage Two: I Tire of This!",0,0,0,2,{"wago"},"When Sinestra is brought to 30% health, she draws upon ambient energy to restore her power and erects a shield to protect herself.",12,3235,0,0,168,3245,9,0,0},
    {3235,"A Clash of Flame and Twilight",0,0,0,2,{"wago"},"The red dragon Caelestrasz, Calen in his humanoid form, comes to the party's aid and engages in a magical duel with Sinestra. The duelist with the most mana gains the upper hand.",12,3236,0,0,168,3238,10,3234,0},
    {3236,"Pyrrhic Focus",135817,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Calen burns his own health reserves to restore his mana. His focus also increases healing done to Calen by $87323s2%.",12,0,0,4,168,3237,11,3235,0},
    {3237,"Mana Barrier",136153,2,0,2,{"wago"},"A powerful barrier envelops Sinestra, continually replenishing any lost health at the expense of her mana.",12,0,0,2,168,0,12,3235,0},
    {3238,"Pulsing Twilight Egg",0,1,0,2,{"wago"},"Sinestra has stored vast reserves of twilight energy in these massive eggs.",12,3308,35318,0,168,3239,13,3234,0},
    {3239,"Twilight Spitecaller",0,1,0,2,{"wago"},"These twilight dragonkin periodically stream into the room during the clash between Calen and Sinestra.",12,3240,36137,0,168,3242,15,3234,0},
    {3240,"Unleash Essence",425958,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The Twilight Spitecaller releases a torrent of twilight energy that afflicts all nearby enemies, inflicting damage equal to $90028s1% of each target's maximum health every $90028t1 sec.  Conventional interrupts cannot prevent the casting of the spell, but other effects that cause loss of control may be effective.",12,0,0,48,168,3241,16,3239,0},
    {3241,"Indomitable",451167,2,0,2050,{"wago"},"If a Twilight Spitecaller is incapacitated for more than a brief period of time, it regains control through a surge of sheer will. The Spitecaller becomes immune to all bonds and restraints until a player removes this effect, and inflicts $90045s2 Shadow damage and knocks back players within $90045A2 yards.",12,0,0,2048,168,0,17,3239,0},
    {3242,"Twilight Drake",0,1,0,2,{"wago"},"Twilight Drakes swoop in from the sides of the cavern during the clash between Calen and Sinestra.",12,3243,32232,0,168,0,18,3234,0},
    {3243,"Twilight Breath",425954,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The Drake's breath inflicts $90083s1 Shadow damage in a $90083a1 yard 60 degree cone in front of it.",12,0,0,0,168,3244,19,3242,0},
    {3244,"Absorb Essence",136204,2,0,2,{"wago"},"If a Twilight Drake comes into contact with a pool of Twilight Essence, it siphons that energy and causes the pool to shrink and eventually vanish entirely. Each charge of Essence absorbed increases the Drake's damage by $90107s1%, and its health by $90107s2%. This effect stacks.",12,0,0,1,168,0,20,3242,0},
    {3245,"Stage Three: Now Die!",0,0,0,2,{"wago"},"Once the players destroy the Pulsing Twilight Eggs, Sinestra brings her magical duel with Calen to an end and attacks the players with her full fury. Empowered by the twilight eggs from which she reclaims her siphoned energy, Sinestra no longer deals reduced damage.",12,3246,0,0,168,3352,21,0,0},
    {3246,"Essence of the Red",135819,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Calen bestows a blessing of Alexstrasza upon the raid, granting all players $87946s2% melee, ranged, and spell haste, and causing them to regain $87946s1% of their maximum mana per second. Essence of the Red lasts for $87946d.",12,0,0,0,168,3247,22,3245,0},
    {3247,"Wrack",132095,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Sinestra causes a random player to suffer Shadow damage every $89421t1 sec. for $89421d. with the damage taken increasing rapidly. When a player dispels Wrack, it bounces to two nearby allies of the afflicted player. Wrack retains its remaining duration but returns to its original damage values.\n\n\n\nSuccessfully dispelling Wrack instantly finishes the cooldown of the caster's single-target Magic dispel abilities.",12,0,0,164,168,3248,23,3245,0},
    {3248,"Flame Breath",135805,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Sinestra unleashes a torrent of flame that sweeps across her platform, dealing $90125s1 Fire damage to all enemies.",12,0,0,0,168,3249,24,3245,0},
    {3249,"Twilight Slicer",136202,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Sinestra summons two shadowy orbs, each of which fixates on a player and begins to pursue that player. These spheres are linked together by a cutting beam of pure twilight energy that inflicts $92852s1 Shadow damage per $92851t1 sec. to any player who comes into contact with the beam.\n\n\n\nEach sphere also pulses twilight energy, inflicting $92958s1 Shadow damage every $92957t1 sec in a $92958A1 yard radius. The orbs dissipate after $92957d.",12,0,0,48,168,3250,25,3245,0},
    {3250,"Twilight Blast",425959,2,0,2,{"wago"},"When Sinestra cannot reach anyone in melee range, she blasts an enemy for $89280s1 Shadow damage.",12,0,0,0,168,3251,26,3245,0},
    {3251,"Twilight Whelps",0,1,0,2,{"wago"},"Sinestra periodically calls forth a set of five Twilight Whelps to attack intruders.",12,3252,19295,0,168,0,27,3245,0},
    {3252,"Twilight Spit",425954,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The Twilight Whelps spit shadowy bile on their target, inflicting $89299s1 Shadow damage and increasing the target's Shadow damage taken by $89299s2%. This effect stacks.",12,0,0,1,168,3253,28,3251,0},
    {3253,"Twilight Essence",425958,2,0,2,{"wago"},"When a Twilight Whelp dies, the essence instilled in it by Sinestra leaks out, forming a bubbling puddle beneath its corpse. If this essence touches any other dead Twilight Whelp, that Whelp reanimates. Each pool of Twilight Essence expands over time. The pools inflict $88146s2 Shadow damage every $89284t1 sec.",12,0,0,1,168,0,29,3251,0},
    {3264,"Incineration Security Measure",135818,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmatron strikes everyone in the room for $79035s1 Fire damage every $79023t1 sec. for $79023d.",-1,0,0,0,169,3265,15,3207,0},
    {3265,"Acquiring Target",132177,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmatron acquires a random player as a target for his Flamethrower ability. After $79501d. Magmatron channels his Flamethrower on the target, inflicting $79504s1 Fire damage every $79505t1 sec. to all players in front of him for $79505d.",-1,3266,0,0,169,3268,16,3207,0},
    {3266,"Flamethrower",236216,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmatron inflicts $79504s1 Fire damage every $79505t1 sec. to all enemies in front of him for $79505d.",-1,0,0,0,169,3267,17,3265,0},
    {3267,"Encasing Shadows",136194,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Lord Victor Nefarius causes shadows to bind the feet of the Acquired Target, preventing movement until the Flamethrower finishes channeling.",12,0,0,8,169,0,18,3265,0},
    {3268,"Barrier",135806,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmatron's shield absorbs $79582s1 damage. If the Barrier breaks, it releases a gale of flame, inflicting $79617s1 Fire damage to all players.",-1,0,0,2,169,0,19,3207,0},
    {3269,"Chemical Bomb",136182,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Toxitron fires a Chemical Bomb at a random player, creating a Chemical Cloud at their location. The cloud increases the damage taken by any unit in the cloud.",-1,3270,0,0,169,3271,21,3208,0},
    {3270,"Chemical Cloud",136182,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Toxitron's Chemical Cloud increases the damage taken by any unit in the cloud by $80161s1%. $[!5,6\n\n\n\nThe Chemical Cloud also inflicts $80161s2 Nature damage every $80162t1 seconds.$]",-1,0,0,0,169,0,22,3269,0},
    {3271,"Poison Protocol",132107,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Toxitron's Poison Protocol creates a Poison Bomb every $80053t1 seconds. Each Poison Bomb fixates on a random player. A Poison Bomb explodes when it reaches melee range of its target.",-1,3272,0,0,169,3274,23,3208,0},
    {3272,"Poison Bomb",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"The Poison Bombs created by Toxitron's Poison Protocol each fixate on a random player. A Poison Bomb explodes and creates a Poison Puddle when it reaches melee range of its target.",-1,3273,37556,0,169,0,24,3271,0},
    {3273,"Poison Puddle",132107,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Poison Bombs create $80097A1 yard radius Poison Puddles when they explode. The Poison Puddle inflicts $80097s1 Nature damage every $80095t1 sec. on any player standing within the puddle.",-1,0,0,0,169,0,25,3272,0},
    {3274,"Poison Soaked Shell",136066,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Dealing damage to Toxitron's shield inflicts Soaked in Poison on the damaging player.",-1,3454,0,2,169,3275,26,3208,0},
    {3275,"Grip of Death",136157,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Lord Victor Nefarius sometimes teleports to the center of a Chemical Cloud and casts Grip of Death, pulling all players into the cloud.",12,0,0,8,169,0,29,3208,0},
    {3276,"Electrocute",136050,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Throughout the battle, Nefarian electrocutes the entire raid every time he loses 10% of his health. Electrocute generates a massive crackle of lightning that inflicts $81272s1 Nature damage on all players.",-1,0,0,4,174,3277,1,0,0},
    {3277,"Stage One: Rise, Sister!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Nefarian reveals the undead form of his sister, Onyxia, and the two dragons attack the raid.",-1,3278,0,0,174,3291,2,0,0},
    {3278,"Children of Deathwing",134154,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Nefarian and Onyxia attack $78619s1% faster when they are within $78619A1 yards of each other.",-1,0,0,1,174,3279,3,3277,0},
    {3279,"Nefarian",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,3280,0,0,174,3283,4,3277,0},
    {3280,"Hail of Bones",236295,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Before Nefarian lands at the beginning of Stage One, he summons some Animated Bone Warriors. Each summoning inflicts $78684s1 Shadow damage to nearby players within $78864a1 yards.$[!4,6\n\n\n\nIn 25 player raids Nefarian summons additional Animated Bone Warriors.$]",-1,0,0,0,174,3281,5,3279,0},
    {3281,"Shadowflame Breath",132095,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Nefarian's dragon breath inflicts $77826s2 Shadowflame damage to players within a $77826a2 yard long 60 degree cone, and fully recharges the energy of any Animated Bone Warriors in the breath's area.",-1,0,0,0,174,3282,6,3279,0},
    {3282,"Tail Lash",132109,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Nefarian sweeps his tail at any enemies in a 60 degree cone facing behind him, inflicting $77827s1 Physical damage and stunning them for $77827d.",-1,0,0,0,174,3289,7,3279,0},
    {3283,"Onyxia",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,3284,0,0,174,0,14,3277,0},
    {3284,"Electrical Energy",0,0,0,0,{"wago"},"Onyxia gains energy over time and more energy when Nefarian casts Electrocute. If Onyxia reaches full energy, she explodes in an Electrical Overload, killing all players.",-1,0,0,32,174,3285,15,3283,0},
    {3285,"Lightning Discharge",132109,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Onyxia discharges electricity from the orbs along her sides, inflicting $77942s1 Nature damage to targets within $77942A2 yards.",-1,0,0,0,174,3286,16,3283,0},
    {3286,"Shadowflame Breath",132095,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Onyxia's dragon breath inflicts $77826s2 Shadowflame damage to players within a $77826a2 yard long 60 degree cone, and fully recharges the energy of any Animated Bone Warriors in the breath's area.",-1,0,0,0,174,3287,17,3283,0},
    {3287,"Tail Lash",132109,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Onyxia sweeps her tail at any enemies in a 60 degree cone facing behind her, inflicting $77827s1 Physical damage and stunning them for $77827d.",-1,0,0,0,174,3288,18,3283,0},
    {3288,"Electrical Overload",136050,2,0,0,{"wago"},"If Onyxia reaches full energy, she releases a massive Electrical Overload and causes $78999s1 Nature damage to all players.",-1,0,0,16,174,0,19,3283,0},
    {3289,"Animated Bone Warriors",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Early in stage one and before he lands, Nefarian summons Animated Bone Warriors. The skeletons possess an energy bar that depletes over time. They collapse if they run out of energy, but restore energy if struck by Shadowflame Breath or Shadowblaze.",-1,3290,31092,1,174,3295,8,3279,0},
    {3290,"Empowering Strikes",132215,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Animated Bone Warriors grow more powerful over time, increasing their damage dealt by $79330s1% and their movement speed by $79330s2%. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,0,174,0,9,3289,0},
    {3291,"Stage Two: Curse You, Mortals!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"When the players kill Onyxia, Nefarian takes to the air and fills the room with magma except for three platforms. Nefarian then summons a Chromatic Prototype upon each of the platforms.",-1,3299,0,0,174,3292,20,0,0},
    {3292,"Stage Three: You Simply Will Not Die!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"After the players kill all the Chromatic Prototypes, the lava subsides, and Nefarian lands to finish the battle.",-1,3303,0,0,174,0,25,0,0},
    {3295,"Dominion",236295,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Nefarian periodically dominates the mind of random players, seizing control of their bodies for $79318d. Dominated players walk towards a portal that appears. If a Dominated player reach the portal, it kills them.\n\n\n\nDominion grants players access to three special abilities.",12,3296,0,8,174,0,10,3279,0},
    {3296,"Siphon Power",135737,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Dominated players absorb a little of the immense power Nefarian is using to control them to gain the Stolen Power effect.",12,3297,0,8,174,3298,11,3295,0},
    {3297,"Stolen Power",135737,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Dominated players strike back against Nefarian with vengeance and anger, increasing their damage and healing by $80627s1% for $80627d. This effect stacks.",12,0,0,8,174,0,12,3296,0},
    {3298,"Free Your Mind",135740,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Dominated players focus their will to break Nefarian's Dominion over them, which also increases their movement speed by $98932s1% for $98932d.",12,0,0,8,174,0,13,3295,0},
    {3299,"Chromatic Prototype",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"A Chromatic Prototype appears on each platform. They stand in place and cast Blast Nova.",-1,3300,33185,0,174,3301,21,3291,0},
    {3300,"Blast Nova",135807,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Chromatic Prototypes cast Blast Nova, which inflicts $80735s1 Fire damage every $80734t1 sec. to all enemies.",-1,0,0,64,174,0,22,3299,0},
    {3301,"Shadowflame Barrage",236302,2,0,0,{"wago"},"While flying, Nefarian breathes a Shadowflame Barrage at random players, inflicting $78621s1 Shadowflame damage.",-1,0,0,0,174,3302,23,3291,0},
    {3302,"Explosive Cinders",135791,2,0,2,{"wago"},"While flying, Nefarian occasionally targets random players with Explosive Cinders, coating them in explosive residue that inflicts $79339s1 Fire damage every $79339t1 seconds.\n\n\n\nThe residue detonates after $79339d., inflicting $79347s1 Fire damage to players within $79347A1 yards.",12,0,0,8,174,0,24,3291,0},
    {3303,"Shadowflame Breath",132095,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Nefarian's dragon breath inflicts $77826s2 Shadowflame damage to players within a $77826a2 yard long 60 degree cone, and fully recharges the energy of any Animated Bone Warriors in the breath's area.",-1,0,0,0,174,3304,26,3292,0},
    {3304,"Tail Lash",132109,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Nefarian sweeps his tail at any enemies in a 60 degree cone facing behind him, inflicting $77827s1 Physical damage and stunning them for $77827d.",-1,0,0,0,174,3305,27,3292,0},
    {3305,"Shadowblaze Spark",236302,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Nefarian creates a shadowy blaze at a nearby location that spreads quickly, inflicting $81007s1 Shadowflame damage to all enemies within $81007A1 yards and reanimating any Animated Bone Warriors.",-1,0,0,0,174,3306,28,3292,0},
    {3306,"Animated Bone Warriors",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"Animated Bone Warriors can be reanimated in Stage Three. The skeletons possess an energy bar that depletes over time. They collapse if they run out of energy, but restore energy if struck by Shadowflame Breath or Shadowblaze.",-1,3307,31092,0,174,0,29,3292,0},
    {3307,"Empowering Strikes",132215,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Animated Bone Warriors grow more powerful over time, increasing their damage dealt by $79330s1% and their movement speed by $79330s2%. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,0,174,0,30,3306,0},
    {3308,"Twilight Carapace",425952,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The Pulsing Twilight Eggs are normally impervious to all damage. In moments of dire need, Sinestra directly siphons from the eggs and causes their Twilight Carapace to drop temporarily.",12,0,0,2,168,0,14,3238,0},
    {3310,"Magma Spit",237582,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmaw spits a volley of magma at three random players, inflicting $78359s1 Fire damage to each player.$[!4,6\n\n\n\nIn 25 player raids Magmaw spits at eight random players.$]",-1,0,0,0,170,3311,1,0,0},
    {3311,"Pillar of Flame",237582,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmaw barrages the ground beneath a random player's feet with globs of roiling magma. The impacts sunder the ground, causing eruptions that knock players within $77971A1 yards high into the air and inflicting $77971s1 Fire damage every $77970t1 sec. The impacts also spawn multiple Lava Parasites.",-1,3312,0,32,170,3316,2,0,0},
    {3312,"Lava Parasite",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"These slow moving creatures will burrow into the warm flesh of players when they attack, infecting their new host.",-1,3313,37456,0,170,0,3,3311,0},
    {3313,"Parasitic Infection",236197,2,0,0,{"wago"},"When a Lava Parasite burrows into the flesh of a player, the Lava Parasite inflicts $78941s1 damage every $78941t1 sec. for $78941d. After the infection runs its course, the player vomits up the Parasite. It then begins to search for a new host.",-1,0,0,0,170,0,4,3312,0},
    {3314,"Mangle",132278,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmaw picks up his current target in his jaws, then bites down. The crushing force inflicts $89773s1 damage every $89773t1 sec.  Magmaw crushes his target severely after $89773d.  Impaling Magmaw causes him to release his grasp on the target.",-1,3315,0,1,170,3318,7,0,0},
    {3315,"Sweltering Armor",135818,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmaw's fiery jaws melt the armor of the player targeted by Mangle, reducing the player's armor by $78199s1% for $78199d.",-1,0,0,1,170,0,8,3314,0},
    {3316,"Lava Spew",237582,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmaw spews a stream of molten lava across all players, inflicting $77690s1 Fire damage every $77689t1 sec for $77689d.",-1,0,0,0,170,3317,5,0,0},
    {3317,"Molten Tantrum",132352,2,0,0,{"wago"},"If Magmaw is ever unable to reach an enemy with his melee attack, he enters a frenzy. Magmaw then launches Magma Spit at all players and increases his Fire damage dealt by $78403s1% for $78403d. This effect stacks.",-1,0,0,0,170,3314,6,0,0},
    {3318,"Massive Crash",132316,2,0,0,{"wago"},"Magmaw brings his entire body smashing down on one half of the room, inflicting $88287s1 damage and stuns all players caught beneath him for $88287d. The Massive Crash also briefly stuns Magmaw, allowing two players to leap onto his pincers.",-1,0,0,0,170,3319,9,0,0},
    {3319,"Lava Worm Wrangling",0,0,0,0,{"wago"},"Immediately after Magmaw performs Massive Crash, a window of opportunity exists where two players can leap onto his pincers. From that location they can attach chains to the spike protruding from the ground in front of the worm, and then reel Magmaw onto the spike.",-1,3320,0,32,170,3322,10,0,0},
    {3320,"Launch Hook",134226,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The players hanging onto Magmaw's pincers can launch a hook at the spike in front of the worm. If the hook connects, it chains Magmaw to the spike for $77917d. Magmaw will break free from a single connecting chain, but if a player connects a second chain to the spike then the players reel the chains in and impale Magmaw on the spike.",-1,0,0,32,170,3321,11,3319,0},
    {3321,"Point of Vulnerability",132177,2,0,0,{"wago"},"When Magmaw is impaled on the spike, players can attack his exposed and unarmored head. Attacking the exposed head increases the damage dealt to Magmaw by $79011s1%.  Magmaw frees himself from the spike after $77907d.",-1,0,0,2,170,0,12,3319,0},
    {3322,"Lord Victor Nefarius",0,1,0,2,{"wago"},"On Heroic Difficulty Lord Nefarius arrives to observe the adventurers contend with his pet and thwart their efforts.",12,3323,32440,8,170,0,13,0,0},
    {3323,"Blazing Inferno",135789,2,0,2,{"wago"},"Lord Nefarius calls down a meteor of bone and fire at the ground beneath a random player. The meteor inflicts $92154s2 Fire damage to players in a $92154A2 yard radius and knocks them down. The explosion creates a Blazing Bone Construct, and sparks the Ignition of fast-moving flames in a spiral around the point of impact.",12,3324,0,24,170,3328,14,3322,0},
    {3324,"Ignition",132386,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The Blazing Inferno creates moving patches of flame that swirl around the point of impact, inflicting $92134s1 Fire damage every $92131t1 sec to all players within $92134A1 yards of them. The Ignition flames dissipate after $92129d.",12,0,0,8,170,3325,15,3323,0},
    {3325,"Blazing Bone Construct",0,1,0,2,{"wago"},"Lord Nefarius's Blazing Inferno creates a single flaming skeletal construct.",12,3326,37397,8,170,0,16,3323,0},
    {3326,"Fiery Slash",132338,2,0,2,{"wago"},"The construct slashes at an enemy with its fiery claws, dealing $92144s1% of normal melee damage as Fire damage.",12,0,0,8,170,3327,17,3325,0},
    {3327,"Armageddon",135826,2,0,2,{"wago"},"When a Blazing Bone Construct reaches 20% remaining health, it prepares to self-destruct. The Blazing Bone Construct then explodes in an Armageddon, inflicting $92182s2 Fire damage to all players.",12,0,0,26,170,0,18,3325,0},
    {3328,"Shadow Breath",236302,2,0,2,{"wago"},"When Magmaw reaches 30% remaining health, Lord Nefarius begins to directly attack the players. He launches volleys of shadowy flame at random players. The Shadow Breath inflicts $92173s1 Shadow damage to all players within $92173A1 yards of his target.",12,0,0,8,170,0,19,3322,0},
    {3330,"Fieroblast",135808,2,0,0,{"wago"},"The Blazing Talon Initiate hurls a fiery boulder at an enemy, inflicting $101223s1 Fire damage and $101223s2 Fire damage every $101223t2 seconds for $101223d.",-1,0,0,192,194,3331,21,2834,0},
    {3331,"Fire it Up!",512617,2,0,0,{"wago"},"When a Blazing Talon Initiate casts Fieroblast, they gain a stack of Fire it Up! This effect increases the Initiate's damage dealt by $100093s1% and casting speed by $100093s2%.",-1,0,0,0,194,0,22,2834,0},
