    {9955,"Replicate",135888,2,0,1,{"wago"},"Upon death, Replicating Arcane Aberrations split into 7 Arcane Remnants.",-1,0,0,0,1197,0,53,9948,0},
    {9956,"Overview",0,3,0,1,{"wago"},"Imperator Mar'gok assaults players with destructive Arcane magic and summons Arcane Aberrations to fight for him.\n\n\n\nWhen Imperator Mar'gok reaches 85%, 55% and 25% health remaining, he activates one of the runestones in his throne room, augmenting his abilities with additional effects.\n\n\n\nThe runestones activated at 55% and 25% must be awakened from their dormant state. As they charge, guards arrive to defend the Imperator as Volatile Anomalies pour from the stone.$[!16\n\n\n\nIn Mythic difficulty, Imperator Mar'gok maintains the effects of 2 runestones at once and begins to awake a new runestone at 66% and 33% health remaining.$]",-1,9957,0,0,1197,9889,1,0,0},
    {9957,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,1,{"wago"},"$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:156238|h[Arcane Wrath]|h|r spreads to nearby allies.\n\n$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:156467|h[Destructive Resonance]|h|r will inflict lethal damage if triggered.\n\n$bullet;Arcane Aberrations inflict heavy raid wide damage as long as they are alive.",-1,0,0,2,1197,9958,2,9956,0},
    {9958,"Healers",0,3,0,1,{"wago"},"$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:156238|h[Arcane Wrath]|h|r inflicts heavy damage when it expires from a target.\n\n$bullet;Arcane Aberrations will inflict raid wide damage every second that they are alive.\n\n$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:157349|h[Force Nova]|h|r inflicts heavy damage to players as it moves over them.",-1,0,0,4,1197,9959,3,9956,0},
    {9959,"Tanks",0,3,0,1,{"wago"},"$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:159515|h[Accelerated Assault]|h|r will stack indefinitely until Imperator Mar'gok melee attacks a different target.\n\n$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:158605|h[Mark of Chaos]|h|r will inflict damage to allies within 35 yards when it expires.\n\n$bullet;Imperator Mar'gok will periodically summon Arcane Aberrations.",-1,0,0,1,1197,0,4,9956,0},
    {9960,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"Oregorger draws upon his reserves of Blackrock Ore to attack his enemies. When he has spent all his Blackrock Ore, he begins rampaging around in search of new Blackrock Ore to replenish himself. Once Oregorger is sated, he stops rolling and returns to fighting.",-1,9961,0,0,1202,9969,1,0,0},
    {9961,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,1,{"wago"},"$bullet;Interrupt |cFF2959D3|Hspell:156879|h[Blackrock Barrage]|h|r to prevent raidwide damage and slow Oregorger's consumption of Blackrock Ore.\n\n$bullet;Breaking open Ore Crates during Feeding Frenzy will leave Blackrock Ore on the ground for Oregorger to consume.",-1,0,0,2,1202,9962,2,9960,0},
    {9962,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Shielding and using damage mitigating abilities on the closest target of |cFF2959D3|Hspell:156324|h[Acid Torrent]|h|r can decrease the damage dealt to rest of the targets.",-1,0,0,4,1202,9963,3,9960,0},
    {9963,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Position yourself to be closest in the |cFF2959D3|Hspell:156324|h[Acid Torrent]|h|r cone and use damage mitigating abilities to decrease the damage dealt to others.\n\n$bullet;Quickly regain threat after Oregorger leaves his Feeding Frenzy.",-1,0,0,1,1202,0,4,9960,0},
    {9964,"Feeding Frenzy",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"When his Blackrock Ore reserves have depleted, Oregorger rampages through the room, trampling all in his path as he searches for ore to eat.",-1,9968,0,0,1202,0,11,0,0},
    {9965,"Earthshaking Collision",463566,2,155897,0,{"wago"},"$[!16 \n\n\n\n In Mythic difficulty, these collisions also leave Unstable Slag residue at the location of the collision. Unstable Slag explodes if another collision occurs at the same location. $]",-1,0,0,0,1202,9966,13,9964,0},
    {9966,"Hunger Drive",135788,2,155819,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,0,1202,9967,14,9964,0},
