    {19041,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"King Mechagon, a master inventor, unleashes two of his greatest contraptions. Initially, he begins his assault by piloting the Aerial Unit R-21/X.  Once destroyed, King Mechagon unleashes his greatest weapon, the Omega Buster mech suit.",-1,19042,0,0,2331,19874,1,0,0},
    {19042,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Avoid touching |cFF2959D3|Hspell:291915|h[Plasma Orbs]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;Position yourself to avoid hitting other players with |cFF2959D3|Hspell:291928|h[Giga-Zap]|h|r.",-1,0,0,1,2331,19043,2,19041,0},
    {19043,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Avoid touching |cFF2959D3|Hspell:291915|h[Plasma Orbs]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;Position yourself to avoid hitting other players with |cFF2959D3|Hspell:291928|h[Giga-Zap]|h|r.",-1,0,0,4,2331,19044,3,19041,0},
    {19044,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Avoid touching |cFF2959D3|Hspell:291915|h[Plasma Orbs]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;Position yourself to avoid hitting other players with |cFF2959D3|Hspell:291928|h[Giga-Zap]|h|r.",-1,0,0,2,2331,0,4,19041,0},
    {19048,"Section 40",0,2,283524,3,{"wago"},nil,0,0,0,32,2328,18975,25,18974,0},
    {19049,"Section 41",0,2,283540,2,{"wago"},nil,0,0,0,64,2328,18982,44,19060,0},
    {19051,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"Uu'nat battles his enemies using the gift of N'Zoth, offering power and corruption. Only with the three Relics of Power do the forces of Azeroth stand a chance at survival. \n\n\n\nIn stage one, Uu'nat calls upon the many eyes of N'Zoth to blast and confuse players.\n\n\n\nIn stage two, Uu'nat is assisted by waves of N'Zoth's minions who seek to overwhelm their enemies.\n\n\n\nIn stage three, Uu'nat uses the sheer power of N'Zoth's mighty gaze to wither and crush players.",-1,19052,0,0,2332,19055,1,0,0},
    {19052,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Tanks can use |cFF2959D3|Hspell:284804|h[Custody of the Deep]|h|r from the Trident of Deep Ocean to provide shelter and protection to players.\n\n$bullet;Undying Guardians gain strength from |cFF2959D3|Hspell:285310|h[Shroud of Whispers]|h|r and must be kept away from Uu'nat due to |cFF2959D3|Hspell:287692|h[Sightless Bond]|h|r.",-1,0,0,1,2332,19053,2,19051,0},
    {19053,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Damage dealers can use |cFF2959D3|Hspell:284583|h[Storm of Annihilation]|h|r from the Tempest Caller to annihilate Undying Guardians.\n\n$bullet;Interrupt Primordial Mindbenders when they cast |cFF2959D3|Hspell:285427|h[Consume Essence]|h|r to prevent them from healing.",-1,0,0,2,2332,19054,3,19051,0},
    {19054,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Healers can use |cFF2959D3|Hspell:284733|h[Embrace of the Void]|h|r from the Void Stone to deny the healing from |cFF2959D3|Hspell:285185|h[Oblivion Tear]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;Upon activation of the Void Stone, the bearer must take damage to break |cFF2959D3|Hspell:284722|h[Umbral Shell]|h|r and end the effects of |cFF2959D3|Hspell:284733|h[Embrace of the Void]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;Keep health levels high during |cFF2959D3|Hspell:284583|h[Storm of Annihilation]|h|r to prevent |cFF2959D3|Hspell:284620|h[Annihilate]|h|r from destroying players.",-1,0,0,4,2332,0,4,19051,0},
    {19055,"Relics of Power",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},"Players are able to harness the Relics of Power while they are fully charged.",-1,19056,0,0,2332,19926,5,0,0},
    {19056,"Void Stone",0,0,0,0,{"wago"},"Healers can pick up and utilize the Void Stone.",-1,19182,0,4,2332,19057,6,19055,0},
    {19057,"Trident of Deep Ocean",0,0,0,0,{"wago"},"Tanks are able to pick up and utilize the Trident of Deep Ocean.",-1,19184,0,1,2332,19058,10,19055,0},
    {19058,"Tempest Caller",0,0,0,0,{"wago"},"Damage dealers are able to pick up and use the Tempest Caller.",-1,19149,0,2,2332,0,14,19055,0},
    {19059,"Visage from Beyond",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"An ephemeral image that regenerates its own health upon death.",-1,18989,88850,0,2328,0,34,18988,0},
    {19060,"Eldritch Abomination",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},"A ghastly being from the void that grants visions of annihilation.",-1,18981,85923,32,2328,0,42,18980,0},
    {19062,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"Frida empowers herself with various seals, and releases those seals to improve her allies whenever she reaches 100 Energy. Additionally, Frida and her allies work to reduce the size of the battlefield for their enemies, using both |cFF2959D3|Hspell:283579|h[Consecration]|h|r and |cFF2959D3|Hspell:283587|h[Wave of Light]|h|r to do so. Crusader allies provide additional damage and crowd control for Frida, while disciples heal wounded allies.",-1,19063,0,0,2333,19141,1,0,0},
    {19063,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Interrupt any heals you can to avoid enemies regaining too much health.\n\n$bullet;Avoid facing the crusader allies when they cast |cFF2959D3|Hspell:283650|h[Blinding Faith]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;Avoid attacking the boss when they are affected by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:284436|h[Seal of Reckoning]|h|r.",-1,0,0,2,2333,19064,2,19062,0},
    {19064,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:284469|h[Seal of Retribution]|h|r causes the boss's melee attacks to affect all players.\n\n$bullet;Avoid facing the crusader allies when they cast |cFF2959D3|Hspell:283650|h[Blinding Faith]|h|r.",-1,0,0,4,2333,19065,3,19062,0},
    {19065,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Don't let |cFF2959D3|Hspell:283572|h[Sacred Blade]|h|r stack too high.\n\n$bullet;When tanking the adds, move them out of |cFF2959D3|Hspell:283579|h[Consecration]|h|r so they are not affected by its damage reduction.\n\n$bullet;Keep the adds moving to avoid them being hit by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:283587|h[Wave of Light]|h|r.",-1,0,0,1,2333,0,4,19062,0},
    {19066,"Section 5",0,2,283572,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,1,2333,19068,6,0,0},
