    {30079,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"The One-Armed Bandit assaults players while slowly gaining energy. Upon reaching 100 energy, it uses |cFF2959D3|Hspell:461060|h[Spin to Win!]|h|r to call upon Reel Assistants bearing various symbol Tokens. Defeating these assistants and depositing their tokens within the One-Armed Bandit determines the result.\n\n\n\nAfter all of the valid combinations have been rolled, the One-Armed Bandit overloads and takes control of its own reels using |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465309|h[Cheat to Win!]|h|r in a final attempt to destroy its enemies.",-1,30080,0,0,2644,30083,1,0,0},
    {30080,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:460472|h[The Big Hit]|h|r inflicts high damage and leaves behind a |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460474|h[Shocking Field]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;Activating a Shock Coil causes |cFF2959D3|Hspell:473009|h[Explosive Shrapnel]|h|r to inflict high damage and absorb nearby |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460474|h[Shocking Fields]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;If two tokens are not deposited or a repeat combination is detected during |cFF2959D3|Hspell:461060|h[Spin to Win!]|h|r, the One-Armed Bandit uses |cFF2959D3|Hspell:461068|h[Fraud Detected!]|h|r.",-1,0,0,1,2644,30081,2,30079,0},
    {30081,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Reel Assistants called forth from |cFF2959D3|Hspell:461060|h[Spin To Win!]|h|r bear icons that can be slotted back into the One-Armed Bandit.\n\n$bullet;If two tokens are not deposited or a repeat combination is detected during |cFF2959D3|Hspell:461060|h[Spin to Win!]|h|r, the One-Armed Bandit uses |cFF2959D3|Hspell:461068|h[Fraud Detected!]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;Standing close to the |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460181|h[Pay-Line]|h|r chip will grant |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460444|h[High Roller!]|h|r.",-1,0,0,2,2644,30082,3,30079,0},
    {30082,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;If two tokens are not deposited or a repeat combination is detected during |cFF2959D3|Hspell:461060|h[Spin to Win!]|h|r, the One-Armed Bandit uses |cFF2959D3|Hspell:461068|h[Fraud Detected!]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:460164|h[Foul Exhaust]|h|r reduces the movement speed of all players and absorbs a large amount of healing.\n\n$bullet;Standing close to the |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460181|h[Pay-Line]|h|r chip will grant |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460444|h[High Roller!]|h|r.",-1,0,0,4,2644,0,4,30079,0},
    {30083,"Stage One: That's RNG, Baby!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30095,0,0,2644,30086,5,0,0},
    {30085,"Reel Assistant",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,30178,81265,0,2644,30395,34,30095,0},
    {30086,"Stage Two: This Game Is Rigged!",0,0,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30104,0,0,2644,0,50,0,0},
    {30089,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"The Geargrinder begins the encounter encased in |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466615|h[Protective Plating]|h|r, slowly generating energy in preparation for |cFF2959D3|Hspell:471403|h[Unrelenting CAR-nage]|h|r. While atop her war-tank, Vexie calls in Geargrinder Bikers to assist her. When a biker is defeated they surrender their ride, allowing players to unleash a |cFF2959D3|Hspell:459453|h[Blaze of Glory]|h|r and removing an application of |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466615|h[Protective Plating]|h|r. Once all |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466615|h[Protective Plating]|h|r is removed, the Geargrinder suffers a |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460603|h[Mechanical Breakdown]|h|r.\n\n\n\nWhile broken down, Vexie begins to |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460116|h[Tune-Up]|h|r the war-tank and calls Pit Mechanics to |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460153|h[Repair]|h|r the Geargrinder. Once fully repaired Vexie commands the Geargrinder to continue its assault!",-1,31555,0,0,2639,30093,1,0,0},
    {30090,"Tanks",0,3,0,2,{"wago"},"$bullet;Defeated Geargrinder Bikers surrender their bikes, allowing for |cFF2959D3|Hspell:459453|h[Blaze of Glory]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:459627|h[Tank Buster]|h|r leaves an |cFF2959D3|Hspell:468129|h[Oil Slick]|h|r at the caster's location.\n\n$bullet;Vexie's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460116|h[Tune-Up]|h|r and Pit Mechanics' |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460153|h[Repair]|h|r the Geargrinder's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466615|h[Protective Plating]|h|r.",0,0,0,1,2639,30091,3,30089,0},
    {30091,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Defeated Geargrinder Bikers surrender their bikes, allowing for |cFF2959D3|Hspell:459453|h[Blaze of Glory]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;Vexie's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460116|h[Tune-Up]|h|r and Pit Mechanics' |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460153|h[Repair]|h|r the Geargrinder's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466615|h[Protective Plating]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:460603|h[Mechanical Breakdown]|h|r causes the Geargrinder to take increased damage.",-1,0,0,2,2639,30092,4,30089,0},
    {30092,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;Defeated Geargrinder Bikers surrender their bikes, allowing for |cFF2959D3|Hspell:459453|h[Blaze of Glory]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:459666|h[Spew Oil]|h|r inflicts moderate damage to afflicted players.\n\n$bullet;While the Geargrinder suffers from a |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460603|h[Mechanical Breakdown]|h|r all players take damage from |cFF2959D3|Hspell:460386|h[Backfire]|h|r.\n\n$bullet;|cFF2959D3|Hspell:460603|h[Mechanical Breakdown]|h|r causes the Geargrinder to take increased damage.",-1,0,0,4,2639,0,5,30089,0},
