    {30740,"Spawn of Bael'Gar",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,30946,122126,0,2664,0,8,30947,0},
    {30741,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"Lord Incendius summons powerful Flame Geysers that will inflict deadly damage until they are brought under control. Even in defeat, a |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463486|h[Flame Geyser]|h|r casts |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463472|h[Dying Flare]|h|r which can hurl players off the bridge and inflict high damage.\n\n\n\nLord Incendius will attempt to force players off the bridge with |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463495|h[Scorching Wind]|h|r. Tanks will need to work together to prevent |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463499|h[Blowback]|h|r from throwing them off the bridge.\n\n\n\nFlame Geysers that remain when Lord Incendius casts |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463495|h[Scorching Wind]|h|r may become extremely deadly.",-1,30742,0,0,2665,30745,1,0,0},
    {30742,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Flame Geysers become more deadly the longer they are left alive. Each cast of |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463471|h[Blaze]|h|r becomes successively faster.\n\n$bullet; When a Flame Geyser is defeated, players must split the damage caused by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463472|h[Dying Flare]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Taunt Lord Incendius to prevent the other tank from being pushed off the bridge by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463499|h[Blowback]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Be wary of being pushed off the bridge by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463472|h[Dying Flare]|h|r or |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463495|h[Scorching Wind]|h|r.",-1,0,0,1,2665,30743,2,30741,0},
    {30743,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Flame Geysers become more deadly the longer they are left alive. Each cast of |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463471|h[Blaze]|h|r becomes successively faster.\n\n$bullet; When a Flame Geyser is defeated, players must split the damage caused by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463472|h[Dying Flare]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Be wary of being pushed off the bridge by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463472|h[Dying Flare]|h|r or |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463495|h[Scorching Wind]|h|r.",-1,0,0,2,2665,30744,3,30741,0},
    {30744,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463503|h[Consumptive Flames]|h|r inflicts a short burst of high damage.\n\n$bullet; Flame Geysers have the potential to inflict high damage to the entire raid until they are brought under control and defeated.\n\n$bullet; It will be difficult to stop and cast during |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463495|h[Scorching Wind]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Be wary of being pushed off the bridge by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463472|h[Dying Flare]|h|r or |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463495|h[Scorching Wind]|h|r.",-1,0,0,4,2665,0,4,30741,0},
    {30745,"Section 10",0,2,463487,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,0,2665,30746,5,0,0},
    {30746,"Section 9",0,2,463503,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,4,2665,30747,6,0,0},
    {30747,"Section 6",0,2,463486,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30969,0,34,2665,30750,7,0,0},
    {30748,"Section 7",0,2,463471,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,64,2665,30749,9,30969,0},
    {30749,"Section 8",0,2,463472,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,16,2665,0,10,30969,0},
    {30750,"Section 5",0,2,463495,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30970,0,32,2665,0,11,0,0},
    {30751,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"When Golem Lord Argelmach's spirit is released from his mortal coil, he will possess the golems around the Mold Foundry. The golem that is |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464938|h[Possessed]|h|r will gain energy over time. At maximum energy, it will unleash a powerful ability.\n\n\n\nToxitron and Electron are stationary casters, while Magmatron and Arcanatron are powerful melee combatants. Moving the golems too close together will active |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463852|h[Golem Overdrive]|h|r, increasing their combat prowess.",-1,30752,0,0,2666,30783,1,0,0},
    {30752,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Each time Arcanotron's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470014|h[Arcane Overcharge]|h|r is caught, the explosion that occurs when it hits the ground will be reduced.\n\n$bullet; Magmatron's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467919|h[Flamethrower]|h|r can be used to burn away |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463829|h[Chemical Bombs]|h|r before |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463823|h[Incineration]|h|r combusts all of them at once.\n\n$bullet; Moving golems too close together will activate |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463852|h[Golem Overdrive]|h|r.",-1,0,0,1,2666,30753,2,30751,0},
    {30753,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470073|h[Power Generator]|h|r will empower golems or players that intercept the energy orbs moving towards Arcanotron.\n\n$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467918|h[Poison-Soaked]|h|r must be burned away from players with Magmatron's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467919|h[Flamethrower]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Players afflicted by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467926|h[Livewire]|h|r will emit an |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467930|h[Electrical Discharge]|h|r when it is dispelled or expires.\n\n$bullet; Players paired by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463847|h[Lethal Attraction]|h|r must stand together or suffer lethal damage.",-1,0,0,2,2666,30754,3,30751,0},
    {30754,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463823|h[Incineration]|h|r and |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463837|h[Poison Mist]|h|r will inflict heavy damage to the entire raid.\n\n$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467918|h[Poison-Soaked]|h|r must be burned away from players with Magmatron's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467919|h[Flamethrower]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Players afflicted by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467926|h[Livewire]|h|r will emit an |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467930|h[Electrical Discharge]|h|r when it is dispelled or expires.\n\n$bullet; Players paired by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:463847|h[Lethal Attraction]|h|r must stand together or suffer lethal damage.",-1,0,0,4,2666,0,4,30751,0},
    {30755,"Section 5",0,2,470014,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,1,2666,30786,9,30785,0},
    {30756,"Section 5",0,2,463821,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,64,2666,30784,6,30783,0},
    {30757,"Section 5",0,2,463829,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,30987,0,0,2666,30790,16,30789,0},
    {30758,"Section 5",0,2,464485,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,0,2666,0,18,30757,0},
    {30759,"Section 5",0,2,467919,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,30989,0,0,2666,30788,12,30787,0},
    {30760,"Section 5",0,2,463852,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,32,2666,30988,26,0,0},
    {30761,"Section 5",0,2,463847,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,48,2666,0,25,30792,0},
    {30762,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"The Seven alternate between manifesting fully in the physical realm and returning to their ghostly state becoming |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464371|h[Corporeal]|h|r or |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464370|h[Incorporeal]|h|r. While |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464371|h[Corporeal]|h|r, each member of the Seven inflicts and suffers full damage and has access to more powerful abilities. Anger'rel and Gloom'rel will remain |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464371|h[Corporeal]|h|r through the entire encounter while the third |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464371|h[Corporeal]|h|r member of the Seven changes as the encounter progresses. When a member of the Seven reaches full energy, they will use their most powerful ability.",-1,30763,0,0,2667,30766,1,0,0},
    {30763,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Gloom'rel and Anger'rel will remain |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464371|h[Corporeal]|h|r through the entire encounter.\n\n$bullet; Anger'rel will charge a distant player and use |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465652|h[Bladestorm]|h|r when he reaches full energy.\n\n$bullet; Gloom'rel will use |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464361|h[Recklessness]|h|r when he reaches full energy.\n\n$bullet; Each of the Seven have a deadly ultimate ability they will use when they reach maximum energy. The entire raid must respond to these moments in order to defeat the Seven.",-1,0,0,1,2667,30764,2,30762,0},
    {30764,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Three of the Seven will be |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464371|h[Corporeal]|h|r at a time and suffer full damage.\n\n$bullet; Seeth'rel's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464337|h[Blizzard]|h|r creates a deadly hazard targeting a random player.\n\n$bullet; Vile'rel's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464344|h[Power Word: Respite]|h|r creates an absorb that heals its target while it persists.\n\n$bullet; Each of the Seven have a deadly ultimate ability they will use when they reach maximum energy. The entire raid must respond to these moments in order to defeat the Seven.",-1,0,0,2,2667,30765,3,30762,0},
    {30765,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Doom'rel will |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464333|h[Banish]|h|r a random player when he is |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464371|h[Corporeal]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Dope'rel's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:469628|h[Smoke Bomb]|h|r will reduce spell range while it persists.\n\n$bullet; Hate'rel's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464362|h[Magma Burn]|h|r will become deadly if it stacks too high.\n\n$bullet; Each of the Seven have a deadly ultimate ability they will use when they reach maximum energy. The entire raid must respond to these moments in order to defeat the Seven.",-1,0,0,4,2667,0,4,30762,0},
    {30766,"Anger'rel",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30800,122581,1,2667,30769,5,0,0},
    {30767,"Doom'rel",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30806,122582,0,2667,30768,13,0,0},
    {30768,"Dope'rel",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30811,122583,0,2667,30770,18,0,0},
    {30769,"Gloom'rel",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30803,122584,1,2667,30767,9,0,0},
    {30770,"Hate'rel",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30815,122585,0,2667,30771,22,0,0},
    {30771,"Seeth'rel",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30819,122580,0,2667,30772,28,0,0},
    {30772,"Vile'rel",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30822,122586,0,2667,30826,32,0,0},
    {30773,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"General Angerforge commands an army within the Lyceum in defense of the Imperial Throne. Players will need to overcome an array of firepower in order to reach the general.\n\n\n\nHarbingers of Flame channel |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467394|h[World In Flames]|h|r, wreathing all players within the Lyceum in intensifying Fire damage. The Harbingers of Flame cannot be damage until the Shadowforge Braziers are lit using the Shadowforge Torches carried by the Shadowforge Flame Keepers.\n\n\n\nAfter both Shadowforge Braziers are lit, the burning barriers protecting General Angerforge will fall, opening the general up to attack directly.",-1,30774,0,0,2668,30828,1,0,0},
    {30774,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; The |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467394|h[Commanding Aura]|h|r of General Angerforge and Anvilrage Officers drastically increases the combat prowess of nearby Dark Iron.\n\n$bullet; General Angerforge and Anvilrage Officers cast |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466107|h[Shatter Armor]|h|r. It will not be removed until the end of the encounter.\n\n$bullet; Your allies will need to be protected from many different Dark Iron soldiers in order to succeed.",-1,0,0,1,2668,30775,2,30773,0},
    {30775,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Anvilrage Medics will attempt to |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466096|h[Heal]|h|r their allies.\n\n$bullet; Anvilrage Rogues |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466259|h[Fixate]|h|r a player until death.\n\n$bullet; Anvilrage Sappers will |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466273|h[Detonate]|h|r upon reaching a player, inflicting high Physical damage.\n\n$bullet; General Angerforge's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467415|h[Fireburst Grenade]|h|r can be avoided by taking cover behind a column.",-1,0,0,2,2668,30776,3,30773,0},
    {30776,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467394|h[World In Flames]|h|r will continue to deal increasing Fire damage. Defeating a Harbinger of Flames will slow incoming damage.\n\n$bullet; Anvilrage Rogues |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466259|h[Fixate]|h|r a player until death.\n\n$bullet; Anvilrage Sappers will |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466273|h[Detonate]|h|r upon reaching a player, inflicting high Physical damage.\n\n$bullet; The pillars within the Lyceum can be used to avoid |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467423|h[Firing Lines]|h|r and |cFF2959D3|Hspell:467415|h[Fireburst Grenade]|h|r, but will also make it challenging to heal players who move on their own.",-1,0,0,4,2668,0,4,30773,0},
