    {30859,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"Ambassador Flamelash calls upon the denizens of the Firelands to incinerate his foes. When Ambassador Flamelash casts |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464372|h[Open Firelands Portals]|h|r, players must quickly spread in order to defeat Burning Spirits and destroy portal anchors. If too many spirits successfully cast |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464769|h[Fury of the Firelands]|h|r, the damage from Ambassador Flamelash will become overwhelming. Until all portal anchors are destroyed, |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464999|h[Unstable Portal]|h|r will continue to inflict damage to the entire raid.\n\n\n\nWhen Ambassador Flamelash reaches maximum energy, he casts |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470203|h[Cremate]|h|r, which must be split between multiple players. The |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470363|h[Cremation]|h|r left behind by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470203|h[Cremate]|h|r should be quickly dispelled or will overwhelm the raid.",-1,30860,0,0,2669,30976,1,0,0},
    {30860,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet;  Tanks will need to split the damage of |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470203|h[Cremate]|h|r in order to survive, and the |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470207|h[Flamelash]|h|r it leaves behind makes a player more susceptible to Fire damage until it fades.\n\n$bullet;  Firestarter's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464918|h[Explosive Impact]|h|r inflicts heavy Physical damage.\n\n$bullet;  Flamewalkers are a powerful melee combatant that is also capable of casting |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470164|h[Magma Infusion]|h|r.",-1,0,0,1,2669,30861,2,30859,0},
    {30861,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Firestarters should be lured away from the raid. The explosion from |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464983|h[Torch]|h|r is large and inflicts high damage.\n\n$bullet; Flamewalkers cast |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470164|h[Magma Infusion]|h|r until they are defeated, making it more difficult to navigate the Iron Hall.\n\n$bullet; Players should destroy portal anchors as quickly as possible while ensuring Burning Spirits do not successfully cast |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464769|h[Fury of the Firelands]|h|r.",-1,0,0,2,2669,30862,3,30859,0},
    {30862,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Healers should quickly dispel |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470363|h[Cremation]|h|r from players that split the damage of |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470203|h[Cremate]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Tanks afflicted by |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470207|h[Flamelash]|h|r will suffer increased Fire damage.\n\n$bullet; When a Flamewalker is killed, it will depart with an |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470330|h[Explosive Demise]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Incoming damage can quickly become overwhelming during |cFF2959D3|Hspell:464372|h[Open Firelands Portals]|h|r unless the raid manages every threat successfully.",-1,0,0,4,2669,0,4,30859,0},
    {30864,"Section 31",0,2,463967,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,0,2645,30867,89,30870,0},
    {30865,"Section 32",0,2,1215953,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,31500,0,0,2645,0,84,30517,0},
    {30867,"Section 34",0,2,466385,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,0,2645,31650,90,30870,0},
    {30870,"Mug'Zee",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},"Mug'Zee joins forces as the Head Honcho and gains access to all of their abilities from Stage One.",-1,30864,124110,0,2645,0,88,30510,0},
    {30887,"Burning Spirit",0,2,464372,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30889,0,38,2669,0,20,0,0},
    {30889,"Section 11",0,2,464998,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,4,2669,30898,21,30887,0},
    {30890,"Section 13",0,2,470244,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30896,0,0,2669,30984,9,0,0},
    {30894,"Flamewalker",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,30895,122591,0,2669,0,15,30984,0},
    {30895,"Section 18",0,2,470164,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,30985,0,0,2669,31073,16,30894,0},
    {30896,"Firestarter",0,1,0,1,{"wago"},nil,-1,30981,122593,0,2669,0,10,30890,0},
    {30898,"Burning Spirit",0,1,0,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,30899,122592,2,2669,0,22,30887,0},
    {30899,"Section 12",0,2,464769,0,{"wago"},nil,-1,0,0,64,2669,0,23,30898,0},
    {30900,"Overview",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"Emperor Dagran Thaurissan and Princess Moira Bronzebeard are both formidable combatants. Moira's |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466504|h[Shadow Word: Nemesis]|h|r and |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470599|h[Shadow Word: Necrosis]|h|r must be managed carefully or they will overwhelm the raid. Moira will attempt to heal Dagran with |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470605|h[Radiant Infusion]|h|r. \n\n\n\nDagran is a dangerous melee combatant that will |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465077|h[Call Imperial Guard]|h|r and |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465079|h[Call Twilight's Hammer Ambassadors]|h|r to repel the invaders. When Moira is defeated, Dagran will transform into a powerful |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465069|h[Avatar of Flame]|h|r, empowering all his abilities.\n\n\n\nWhen he becomes desperate, Dagran willl |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466332|h[Beseech The Firelord]|h|r to save him. The Avatar of Ragnaros unleashes devastation that will slowly consume the entire room in molten fire until Dagran is defeated. Dagran will no longer call Imperial Guard or Twilight's Hammer Ambassadors to his side once Ragnaros joins the battle.",-1,30901,0,0,2670,30904,1,0,0},
    {30901,"Tanks",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; Moira and Dagran's abilities are more difficult to avoid if they are near one another.\n\n$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465077|h[Imperial Guards]|h|r will arrive in mole machines on both ends of the room.\n\n$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465060|h[Ironfoe's]|h|r multiattack inflicts bursts of physical damage to Dagran's tank.\n\n$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465070|h[Iron Brand]|h|r will become lethal if it stacks too high.\n\n$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465099|h[Fireguard Destroyers]|h|r summoned by the Avatar of Ragnaros are powerful melee combatants in addition to inflicting high Fire damage to the entire raid.",-1,0,0,1,2670,30902,2,30900,0},
    {30902,"Damage Dealers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; If Moira is not defeated quickly, |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466504|h[Shadow Word: Nemesis]|h|r and |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470599|h[Shadow Word: Necrosis]|h|r will overwhelm the raid.\n\n$bullet; |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465079|h[Twilight's Hammer Ambassadors]|h|r inflict high damage with |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465091|h[Pyroblast]|h|r and they must be killed before they finish casting |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466371|h[Moment of Twilight]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; Dagran's abilities will be more difficult to avoid and inflict higher damage when he becomes an |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465069|h[Avatar of Flame]|h|r.\n\n$bullet; The damage of Avatar of Ragnaros' |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465225|h[Volcanic Blast]|h|r must be split and it will create |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466382|h[Volcanic Stone]|h|r beneath the target's feet.\n\n$bullet; When a Fireguard Destroyer is destroyed, it will erupt in a |cFF2959D3|Hspell:465268|h[Fiery Demise]|h|r.",-1,0,0,2,2670,30903,3,30900,0},
    {30903,"Healers",0,3,0,0,{"wago"},"$bullet; If |cFF2959D3|Hspell:466504|h[Shadow Word: Nemesis]|h|r is dispelled, it will jump to two players. Try to delay removal as long as possible.\n\n$bullet; When |cFF2959D3|Hspell:470599|h[Shadow Word: Necrosis]|h|r is passed, it will inflict raid wide damage, but target's cannot be healed while they suffer from it.\n\n$bullet; Dagran's tank will suffer frequent burst of high damage.\n\n$bullet; Once the Avatar of Ragnaros is summoned, the damage to the raid will spike significantly. All of his abilities inflict raid wide damage.",-1,0,0,4,2670,0,4,30900,0},
